<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>[ 36 ] Claret , L. and Hughes , C. ( 2000 ) Rapid turnover of FlhD and FlhC , the # agellar regulon transcriptional-activator proteins , during Proteus swarming .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11731137" target="_blank">11731137</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>When FlhD and FlhC proteins were synthesized together , accumulation of both proteins by the depletion of ClpXP protease was conﬁrmed ( lane 2 in Fig 4B or 4C ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12675803" target="_blank">12675803</a>]<br></li>
<li>Prüss and Matsumura also demonstrated that FlhD in the absence of FlhC is a regulator of cell division ( 103 ) , and this regulation occurs through induction of the acid response gene cadA , encodong lysine decarboxylase ( 101 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11104815" target="_blank">11104815</a>]<br></li>
